S'MyCards Lite is a tool to track and categorize your spending.How are we different?MyCards Lite monitors SMSes sent to mobile devices by banks, after each card transaction. This is used to create a picture of your spending habits and patterns, grouped by card and category.Bought a new gadget or a fashion accessory with your card ? Now flaunt your special purchases along with the picture of your gadget on Facebook and Twitter.  MyCards Lite now allows you to share picutres of your purchases along with your comments on Facebook or Twitter. MyCards Lite raises alerts if multiple transactions happen at the same vendor within a short span of time. It also records the location of your smart phone while a card is being used to alert you if a transaction occurs at remote locations that are not in your usual pattern.None of the SMSes are modified. All analysis is performed on-device and data remains stored ONLY locally on your device. MyCards Lite will NEVER access your bank account or send out data from your SMSes to external parties. Your data is safe on your smartphone as it is stored locally and ONLY on your device. You need NOT configure your bank credentials as we use only SMSes to track and categorise the spending/payments.At this point, we support the following banks in India:\xe2\x80\xa2Citibank\xe2\x80\xa2HDFC Bank\xe2\x80\xa2IDBI Bank\xe2\x80\xa2IndusInd Bank\xe2\x80\xa2ICICI Bank\xe2\x80\xa2Kotak Bank\xe2\x80\xa2SBI\xe2\x80\xa2Barclays\xe2\x80\xa2Standard Chartered\xe2\x80\xa2American Express\xe2\x80\xa2HSBC Bank\xe2\x80\xa2Axis BankWe are working towards supporting more banks. If your bank is not supported, send us an email with the name of your bank along with a sample sms that you received from the bank about the transaction.How to use MyCards Lite ?1.Upon launching the app for the first time, you will be prompted to sign up. Please choose a username and password for future secure logins to MyCards Lite.2.Login to MyCards Lite after sign up:a.MyCards Lite will first look through all the SMSes locally stored on your smartphone.b.Next, you will be presented with a list of multiple cards whose SMSes fit the above banks\xe2\x80\x99 patternsc.You will now be asked to choose the cards that you want to track.d.Select the cards and click \xe2\x80\x9cSave\xe2\x80\x9d.e.Click on a card to configure additional parameters like card limits, expiry date etc.f.You can come back to this screen at any point from the Settings option.3.You are now all set to use the app. You can track your expenses from the \xe2\x80\x9cExpenditure\xe2\x80\x9d section and payments from the \xe2\x80\x9cPayments\xe2\x80\x9d section. Card Limit feature helps you to know your current spending with respect to your card limit. You can control your expenditure if you are nearing your limit.To delete an entry, long press on it.4.Tagging and categorization:In the \xe2\x80\x9cExpenditure\xe2\x80\x9d section, you can view individual SMSes and their corresponding transactions.You can tag your spending by clicking on the \xe2\x80\x98Tag\xe2\x80\x99 icon. This will bring up a list of available tags. Choose one of them to categorize the expense under the chosen tag. This will be reflected both in the individual SMS view and in the Pie-Chart view5.Need more help or have a suggestion, use the Feedback section to reach us. You can alternatively send us an email at support@intermediasoftech.com for any support or feature requests.Recent changes:1. Did you love or hate the last purchase experience at the restaurant or a mall. Share your emotions with friends on facebook and twitter with pictures.2. Be a consumer activist to comment on the customer experience at point of purchase with photo or text. You can help buying community.3. Many more bank cards added including your account activities 4. A few other improvements'
